## Key Rules

### API (Bun + Hono)
- Config is loaded once in `loadConfig()` — never read env vars directly in handlers
- All modules are initialized in `bootstrap.ts` in the correct order
- HTTP handlers return `{"data": ...}` on success, `{"error": "..."}` on failure
- Auth middleware reads Bearer token from `Authorization` header

### Frontend (Vite + React)
- API client is in `src/lib/api.ts` — use `api.get()`, `api.post()` etc.
{{- if .HasModule "auth"}}
{{- if eq (.ImplFor "auth") "better-auth"}}
- Auth is handled by Better Auth — use the `authClient` from `src/lib/auth.ts`
{{- else if eq (.ImplFor "auth") "clerk"}}
- Auth is handled by Clerk — use `useUser()` hook for client components
{{- end}}
{{- end}}
- Routes are defined with react-router-dom in `src/routes.tsx`

### Development
- `make setup` — install deps + start infra
- `make dev` — start API + web concurrently
- `make test` — run Bun tests
- `make lint` — lint API + frontend

